<br>
I typically hunt the 5 spawns in the tower.  Here is how I do it….<br>
<br>
First – I’m not KOS to the wyverns,  this is important only in that it makes things so much easier – else you will have to deal with getting jumped a lot.  Plus it lets me bind in the tower in case I need to excape to ss.  Once healed and FM  I just gate back<br>
<br>
IF the tower is at a full spawn when I get there,  I summon a MS2 pet just a ways down the first  ramp to the tower ( between the boulder and the first ramp – once there you will see what I mean)  and tell it to guard.  I do all the normal preps like burnout and Ds – then lev myself and head into the tower to pull.<br>
<br>
At 52 I’m able to single pull the wyverns with cancel magic – so get to the edge of the tower and cast on one of the critters.  I then run off the tower with it chasing – usually getting a hit or two on me before it drops to were the bulthorks are on the beach.  Just run to your pet and wait for it – send pet in and your done.  Pet can handle em solo in most cases – just remember to nuke for exp.<br>
<br>
After the fight – reclaim until full mana and do it again until the tower is cleared.<br>
<br>
Once tower is cleared, get your butt up there and  camp it.  Cast a pet and get ready to kill in the same order you took to clear the tower.  Not sure what the spawn rate is, but it’s quick enough. <br>
<br>
Are there troubles?  Sure there is.   Sometimes you get there and the tower is cleared already, usually by that druid/wizard quading.   This means that the next spawn may be a double.  Not a problem.  I don’t even do my full spawn clearing tactic (above) for this and just send the pet in on the two.  When  pet starts getting low I burn down his current target and if it still looks like he is not going to make it – chain another pet.   I’ve managed 4 this way. ( did a double, after one was killed another spawned…after that was killed another spawned again)  As long as you don’t panic you can handle most any situation here.  After all – if worse comes to worse, you can just click on the portal to SS and be gone – no chance of interruption like gating has.  This also can be trouble though, I recommend targeting with hotkeys as clicking the wrong area in the tower will have you ported to Skyshrine.  Not dangerous (unless kos) but damn annoying – especially if you were almost done with a kill.  I did this 5 times one night in a half-hour period. grrrrrrr<br>
<br>
<br>
In between fights I reclaim to FM and if it looks like there is time (depending on how fast you cleared) I grab a wyvern from the nearby area – since I’m bound in the tower getting back is no trouble.  <br>
<br>
I’ve only ever seen the tower camped once, and that was by a fellow looking for stingers.  He let me have the camp for the exp and I just told him when a stinger dropped.  I think many classes are worried about the 5 spawns here, and the druids/wizards only pull OUT of the tower as they need the room to kite.  The generally don’t pull a single as it’s not as mana efficient as 4 are,  so only come in look around and leave in most cases.<br>
<br>
I can’t quad – and I got tired of trying to find a spawn along the ridge areas as they seem to get taken by quaders as soon as they pop.  I’ve even had someone take a mob I was casting on because they tagged it before my spell completed. ( when asking GM's about this it was a matter of who landed a spell first and i was out of luck ) So I do not feel bad camping the tower and tying up the spawns.  Keep the spawn broken and no one will bother you as not many are interested in just a “Single”<br>
<br>
<br>
Mages Rock !<br>
<br>
Urzah<br>
52 mage - Innoruuk<br>
